comment.narrative:
- 16 MCHPs were assessed by 2 joint teams of DHMTs and UNDP on the basis of community participatory mapping/needs assessment utilizing the MOHS structural guidelines; 
- 12 community MCHPs of utmost refurbishment/upgrading needs were identified for project inclusion; 

- The male and female youth of 503 were benefitted from cash for work for MCHPs rehabilitation/construction and procurement of local building materials; 
- Capacity and overall functionality of the 12 community village development committees (VDCs) and facility management committees (FMCs) were assessed as a means of gauging community preparedness for project implementation; 
- 60 gender inclusive monitoring teams (5 males +5 females per team) were formed not only to strengthen monitoring and reporting mechanism during the period of implementing infrastructural works, but also to increase their ownership of the community MCHPs; 
- Groundwork for rehabilitation of 6 MCHP main buildings and 3 staff quarters and for construction of 3 staff quarters completed (including BOQs, procurement of construction materials); 
- 503 youths benefited from cash for work of rehabilitation/construction and procurement of local building materials; 
- Local awareness of hygiene and sanitation was heightened by the distribution of IEC materials (150 caps/T-shirts and 7 banners); Local awareness (1500 people in total of which 628 of girls/women) of toiletry sanitation and hygiene was raised in 6 communities by the conduct of commemorating the World Toilet Day in collaboration with DHMT; 
- 568 females (+ 117 males) gained knowledge about health care financial management through financial literacy training; 18 Women Village Saving and Loan Association Groups (VSLAs) were established and provided with start-up kits; 
- 3 monitoring visits conducted: one for conducting PHUs assessment and the other for inception meeting with implementing partner and stakeholders; 
- Community-based inception meeting conducted in 5 project target communities; 
- 12 out-reach activities completed and confirmed a total catchment population of 73,734 for 12 PHUs to be benefited.

- 12 additional community structures and health facility supported; 
- Capacity of 12 additional community health/development committee will be strengthened; 

- 12 additional infrastructural development plans will be developed; 
- 12 new gender inclusive health infrastructural monitoring teams will be established.
- Up to 12 health facility PHUs/MCHPs) will be rehabilitated(at least one project per community/health facility); 
- 12,000 (1,000 people per community); 
- 12 (at least one health promotion material per health facility); 
- 12 women savings scheme established (at least 2 per community).

